{
  "id": "class_0011",
  "name": "Brine Cartographer",
  "title_completion": "a Brine Cartographer",
  "flavor_text": "Every border wall has its seams, and she has memorized each one \u2014 not with ink, but with salt. She charts the slow corrosion of iron checkpoints, letting brine seep through cracks that no inspector thought to measure. By the time the toll collectors notice the rust, the crossing has already been made.",
